Hey Paul,<br><br>
This site has been a chance to explain how I feel about the war.<br><br>
Each daym, for me, has been a repetition of moments and scenes relived. Over and over.<br><br>
The problem, for many years, was there was no one who wanted to listen - at least not as often as I would have liked.<br><br>
One of your first posts dealt with how you liked to use the positive aspects of Vietnam in a way that would enhance your life. I can't think of a better way to be. Being a vet has always been something which I have used as a resource - something to draw upon when I needed a boost.<br><br>
Healing? I think, first off, the talking and the reminiscing goes a long way in healing *myself*. Then, by encouraging others to be proud and thankful for all they have; we are able to help in someone else's healing.<br><br>
It all goes hand in hand. We are in this together. The Internet helps us to realize the vast numbers of guys who are communicating with each other for, perhaps, the first time.<br><br>
Peace.
